cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE. 

The paper discusses fundamental problems in artificial intelligence, which suggests cs.AI as the most likely sub-category. The use of universal hashing and SAT solving also suggests cs.LG and cs.PL as possible sub-categories. The paper also deals with scaling to larger instances, which could fall under cs.DS. Finally, the mention of constrained-random verification suggests cs.SE as a possible sub-category.
